4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a civil action for an injury
6 arising from a sex offense to a victim with certain
7 disabilities, including being under the age of
8 majority, must be brought within six years of the
9 termination of the victim's disability.
10 This bill would further provide for the statute
11 of limitations for a civil action for an injury arising
12 from a sex offense when the action is brought against
13 the actual alleged perpetrator of the sex offense.
14
15
16 A BILL
17 TO BE ENTITLED
18 AN ACT
19
20 Relating to commencement of actions; to amend Section
21 6-2-8, Code of Alabama 1975; to further provide for the
22 statute of limitations for civil actions involving certain sex
23 offenses.
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
25 Section 1. Section 6-2-8, Code of Alabama 1975, is
26 amended to read as follows:
27 "§6-2-8
28 (a)(1) If anyone an individual is entitled to: (i)
