29 commence any of the actions enumerated in this chapter,; (ii)
30 to make an entry on land; or (iii) enter a defense founded on
31 the title to real property is, and at the time the right
32 accrues, is below the age of 19 years of age, or insaneof
33 unsound mind, he or she shall have three years, or the period
34 allowed by law for the commencement of an action if it be is
35 less than three years, after the termination of the disability
36 to commence an the action, make entry, or defend.
37 (2) No disability shall extend the period of
38 limitations so as to allow an action to be commenced, entry
39 made, or defense made after the lapse of 20 years from the
40 time the claim or right accrued.
41 (3) Nothing in this section shall be interpreted as
42 denying any imprisoned person individual the right to commence
43 an action enumerated in this chapter and to make any proper
44 appearances on his or her behalf in such actions.
45 (b)(1) If anyone an individual entitled to commence any
46 of the actions enumerated in this chapter is, at the time the
47 right accrues, is below the age of 19 years of age, or
48 insaneof unsound mind, and the injury upon which the action is
49 based arises from a sex offense as described in Section
50 15-20A-5, he or she shall have six years after the termination
51 of the disability to commence the action.
52 (2)a. Notwithstanding subdivision (1), in an action
53 against the actual alleged perpetrator of a sex offense as
54 described in Section 15-20A-5, an individual shall have the
55 greater of the following to commence an action under this
56 subsection: (i) 20 years after the termination of the
Page 2

subsection: (i) 20 years after the termination of the
HB108 INTRODUCED
57 disability; or (ii) two years after the criminal conviction or
58 guilty plea of the alleged perpetrator.
59 b. Either time period shall toll during any criminal
60 prosecution of the underlying offense. The tolling shall begin
61 on the date of indictment, presentment, or information.
62 c. An action may be commenced pursuant to this
63 subdivision regardless of the age of the plaintiff at the time
64 the action is commenced.
65 d. This subdivision shall not apply to an action
66 against any party other than the alleged perpetrator of a sex
67 offense, without regard to the doctrine of respondeat superior
68 or any other form of vicarious liability.
69 (c) When both disabilities coexist at the time the
70 claim accrued, the limitation does not attach until both are
71 removed.
72 (d) A disability which that did not exist when a claim
73 accrued does not suspend the operation of the limitation
74 unless the contrary is expressly provided."
75 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
76 1, 2026.
